column10:
Just played through the main campaign and I have to say, this game streamlined the looter shooter content that I came to know and love through the mainline series and added some spicy improvements I hope remain in mainline (I'm looking at you, spells). The endgame is repetitive, but every BL game has had a repetitive endgame. DLC is heckin' overpriced, but Gearbox is a AAA game studio, so I don't know what people expect. Its definitely queer as f***, so if you're one of those hard right snowflakes who throws their laptop at the wall for that sort of thing, go get some therapy. Its nice to see the staff who makes these games a reality making content that they want to make. 
TLDR;
All in all I'd say a solid 8/10, I'd play with friends again.
